Obtain labels of edges in a network

Source: R/getEdgeLabel.R
getEdgeLabel.Rd

The `getEdgeLabel` function generates the labels of edges in a network upon being supplied names of the nodes in the network.

getEdgeLabel(node)

Arguments

node

A numeric or character vector, which contains the names of all nodes in a network.

Value

A character vector of edge labels for each transcriptional network, which can be used as an input of the `getGeneSetEdgeGroup` function. The label or the name of an edge is denoted in the format of i-j, where i-j denotes an edge that connects node i and node j in the network of interest.
